The South West chapter of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP)  has promised to commence a full campaign to reclaim Ekiti and Osun states in the  2022 polls. This was part of the Resolutions reached on Sunday after a stakeholders meeting chaired by the National Vice Chairman, Hon. Olasoji Adagunodo at the party’s  Osuntokun  zonal office Bodija, Ibadan  Oyo State . A statement made available to the Independent Newspapers by the Zonal Publicity Secretary of the party, Chief Sanya Atofarati reaffirmed the determination of the PDP to return to power in Nigeria by using Osun and Ekiti as a litmus test. PDP Southwest Reps Caucus Hails  Zonal Congress ‘Why National Legal Adviser Must Not Destroy Southwest… The zonal office congratulated the party’s Flagbearer in Ekiti State, Otunba Bisi Kolawole, promising to team up with him to reclaim Ekiti in the June 18 governorship poll. The meeting was attended by not less than 22 members, including zonal officers. It urged Ekiti people to kick start the rescue mission by voting for PDP in the forthcoming poll. The party, however, stated that it was prepared to akin to the yearnings of Nigerians to return the nation to the path of good governance as typified by the former  PDP administration at the centre. It also reiterated its commitment to the unity of the party in Ekiti and Osun States ahead of the 2022 governorship elections in the two sister states. The zonal office expressed its strong readiness to collaborate with the determined efforts of Gov. Seyi Makinde and other PDP leaders, to rescue Nigeria from the claws of the directionless APC administration, both at the national and other states controlled by the party in the region.